LOKOJA – The founder and chairperson of the Doyin and Susan Foundation, Chief (Mrs) Adedoyin Eshanumi, has felicitated the Muslim faithful on the occasion of the Eid-el-Kabir celebration. In her felicitation message made available to journalists on Tuesday, Chief Adedoyin congratulated and celebrated with Muslim brothers and sisters in this year’s Eid-el-Kabir celebration. ”As the whole world celebrates the Eid-el-Kabir, I urge Nigerian Muslims to prioritize the nation’s unity and security in their prayers. ”I admonish all to uphold the significance of Eid as portrayed by prophet Mohammed (SAW) which was embedded in his obedient act to God and most especially his humble sacrifice,” she said. Adedoyin, a former APC Kogi West Senatorial Aspirant, noted that only through unity, love and sacrifice that the nation could achieve national progress and the desired developments. ”May this special day bring peace, happiness and prosperity to our dear State, Nigeria and the world at large. ”Happy Eid Mubarak to our Muslim brothers and sisters!”